---
import Header from "../../components/company/CompanyHeader.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/company/CompanyFooter.astro";

const LAST_UPDATED = "January 5, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>LEGAL & TRANSPARENCY | STRUX</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway:wght@300;400;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
      :root {
        --color-bg: #000000;
        --color-text: #FFFFFF;
        --color-muted: #888888;
        --color-border: #222222;
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        color: var(--color-text);
        font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      .container { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 40px; }

      /* --- HERO --- */
      .hero {
        padding: 160px 0 60px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      }
      
      .meta-badge {
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        color: var(--color-muted);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-weight: 700;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      .hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(50px, 8vw, 90px);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -4px;
        line-height: 0.9;
        margin: 0 0 20px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .hero p { color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 18px; max-width: 600px; }

      .toc { display: flex; gap: 30px; margin-top: 40px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .toc-link {
        color: var(--color-text);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        transition: opacity 0.3s;
      }
      .toc-link:hover { opacity: 0.5; }

      /* --- CONTENT --- */
      .legal-card {
        padding: 80px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        scroll-margin-top: 100px;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 42px;
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -1px;
        margin: 0 0 40px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      h3 { 
        font-size: 18px; 
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #FFF; 
        margin: 40px 0 20px; 
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      p, li { 
        font-size: 17px; 
        color: var(--color-muted); 
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      ul { margin: 0 0 30px; padding-left: 20px; }
      li { margin-bottom: 12px; }
      
      a { color: #FFF; text-decoration: underline; }

      /* Accent Box */
      .box {
        padding: 40px;
        background: #0A0A0A;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        margin: 40px 0;
        border-left: 4px solid #FFF;
      }
      .box h4 { margin: 0 0 16px 0; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 1px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #FFF; }
      .box p { margin: 0; font-size: 16px; color: #EEE; }

      @media(max-width: 768px) {
        .container { padding: 0 20px; }
        .hero { padding: 120px 0 40px; }
        .section-title { font-size: 32px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <Header />

    <main class="container">
      <section class="hero">
        <span class="meta-badge">LAST UPDATED: {LAST_UPDATED}</span>
        <h1>LEGAL &<br/>TRANSPARENCY</h1>
        <p>Our commitment to secure, local-first development. Understand your rights and responsibilities.</p>
        
        <nav class="toc">
          <a class="toc-link" href="#privacy">Data & Privacy</a>
          <a class="toc-link" href="#fair-use">Usage Limits</a>
          <a class="toc-link" href="#liability">Liability</a>
          <a class="toc-link" href="#terms">Subscription</a>
        </nav>
      </section>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <article id="privacy" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Data Privacy & Storage</h2>
          
          <div class="box">
            <h4>LOCAL-FIRST ARCHITECTURE</h4>
            <p>Strux is designed with security as a priority. The applications, code, and interfaces you create are <strong>stored locally on your device</strong>. We do not have access to your project files.</p>
          </div>

          <h3>1. Project Data (On Device)</h3>
          <p>Every app you build, every line of JSON, and every UI layout remains in your device's sandbox storage. Unlike web-based builders, your intellectual property never leaves your phone unless you explicitly choose to export or share it. Currently, there are no community sharing features, ensuring your work remains 100% private.</p>

          <h3>2. Account Metadata (Secure Cloud)</h3>
          <p>We use a secure, encrypted cloud infrastructure solely to manage your subscription status and usage quotas. We store the required datas: your anonymous User ID, name, email and your daily credit balance.</p>
        </article>

        <article id="fair-use" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Fair Usage & Limits</h2>
          <p>Strux utilizes advanced AI models to help you generate apps from text. To ensure the service remains fast and sustainable for everyone, we enforce specific usage tiers.</p>

          <h3>Free Tier Limits</h3>
          <p>Users on the Free Tier are provided with <strong>1 (one) AI generation right</strong> to test the capabilities of the system. This allows you to experience the "Text-to-App" feature before committing to a subscription.</p>

          <h3>Pro Tier Limits</h3>
          <p>Subscribing to Strux Pro unlocks "Unlimited App Creation" in terms of project storage. However, for AI-assisted generation, a fair usage policy applies:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Daily Limit:</strong> Pro users are allocated <strong>5 (five) AI generation rights per day</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Reset:</strong> This quota resets automatically every 24 hours.</li>
            <li><strong>Manual Creation:</strong> You can always create and edit unlimited apps manually without using AI credits.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article id="liability" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">User Liability & Responsibility</h2>
          
          <div class="box">
            <h4>STRUX IS A TOOL, YOU ARE THE CREATOR</h4>
            <p>Just like a hammer can build a house or break a window, Strux is a neutral development tool. You are solely responsible for what you build with it.</p>
          </div>

          <h3>1. Content Responsibility</h3>
          <p>You agree that you are the sole creator of the applications built within Strux. <strong>Ashak Studios accepts no liability</strong> for the function, content, or intent of the apps you create.</p>

          <h3>2. Prohibited Activities</h3>
          <p>You strictly agree <strong>NOT</strong> to use Strux to create:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Malicious applications (malware, spyware, viruses).</li>
            <li>Phishing tools or deceptive interfaces intended to steal user data.</li>
            <li>Apps that violate local laws or promote illegal activities.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Any user found creating malicious content will have their access revoked immediately without refund.</p>
        </article>

        <article id="terms" class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="section-title">Subscription & Terms</h2>
          
          <h3>1. Strux Pro Subscription</h3>
          <p>Strux Pro is offered as a monthly subscription service (e.g., $19.99/month) processed entirely by Apple. Upgrading removes all advertisements and unlocks the Pro features listed above.</p>

          <h3>2. Cancellation & Refunds</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Auto-Renewal:</strong> Your subscription automatically renews unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li><strong>Cancellation:</strong> You can cancel anytime directly from your iPhone Settings (Apple ID > Subscriptions). You will retain access until the billing cycle ends.</li>
            <li><strong>Refunds:</strong> All payments are handled by Apple. We (the developers) do not have the ability to issue refunds directly. Please contact Apple Support for billing issues.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3. Contact Us</h3>
          <p>For support regarding the app functionality: <a href="mailto:contact@ashak.co">contact@ashak.co</a></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>